[Equine influenza [EI], an OIE-listed disease, is not notifiable in the UK. In the country's last available annual disease situation report to the OIE (2017), the disease was included among the diseases "present in the country," under the status "infection/infestation." In previous detailed annual reports, the disease was reported as present, without epidemiological statistics presented.

The identification of EI virus strain H3N8 Florida clade 1, apparently new to the UK, as the causative agent of the current event may deserve being discussed as warranting notification to the OIE according to chapter 1.1 of OIE's Terrestrial Animal Health Code, Article 1.1.3.1.c ("1st occurrence of a new strain of a pathogenic agent of a listed disease, infection, or infestation in a country, a zone, or a compartment") or Article 1.1.3.1.d ("a sudden and unexpected change in the distribution or increase in incidence or virulence of, or morbidity or mortality caused by, the pathogenic agent of a listed disease, infection, or infestation present within a country, a zone, or a compartment"). - Mod.AS

